legacy.full_text: 🇿🇼Deputy Minister of Industry and Commerce Mr.R.Bhila @Min_of_IC led a delegation of 50 officials and entrepreneurs to attend the 6th CIIE, launched the Country Exhibition of Zimbabwe, and addressed the sub-forum on Promoting Int’l Cooperation and Innovation in Industrial Parks. https://t.co/1chcItoAcz

The 6th China Int’l Import Expo(CIIE)is taking place in Shanghai from Nov 5-10. Chinese President Xi Jinping sent a congratulatory letter to #CIIE, reaffirming 🇨🇳's commitment to high-level opening up. Premier Li Qiang delivered a keynote speech at the opening ceremony of #CIIE. https://t.co/CUnlgU2jSc
The 6th #CIIE is expected to attract guests from 154 countries, regions & int’l organizations. More than 3,400 exhibitors & 394,000 professional visitors have registered to attend the event.

legacy.full_text: Amb. Zhou Ding, Hon. J. Moyo, Minister of @OMpslsw & Dr T. Wushe, Permanent Secretary of @Min_of_IC addressed the Opening Ceremony of Zimbabwe Chinese Enterprises Job Fair 2023. They underscored the important role played by 🇨🇳 enterprises in promoting 🇿🇼’s economic & social devt. https://t.co/jtM83QUHCs

The Job Fair, running until Saturday,  builds an open, direct & two-way selection platform for Chinese enterprises & Zimbabwean youth. Hope job seekers could fully demonstrate their talents and get appropriate jobs. https://t.co/gODuNCAlcy

As ZIDA’s Q3 Report shows, 🇨🇳has remained as 🇿🇼’s largest investor, with investment totaled at US$3.74 billion from Q1-Q3 2023, accounting for 71.5% of 🇿🇼's total FDI and DDI. Projected investment from 🇨🇳reached US$2.79 billion and 280 new Chinese investors came in Q3 2023. https://t.co/9jbzVPDB1w
https://t.co/TmLrPEcjkM

The report “Chinese Investment in Africa 2023” reveals that Chinese companies have carried out infrastructure projects worth over $400 bn in Africa. China is Africa’s 1st trading partner & 4th largest source of investment. https://t.co/jhJT0mnz3s

RT @China_Amb_Zim: Great pleasure to meet Hon. Minister Kirsty Coventry. Minister Coventry recalled her good memory as the gold medal winne…

Great pleasure to meet Hon. Minister Kirsty Coventry. Minister Coventry recalled her good memory as the gold medal winner in 2008 Beijing Olympics. Both of us expressed our commitment to a more in-depth & fruitful cooperation between 🇨🇳&🇿🇼 in sports & cultural areas. https://t.co/IGsDtEfRjr

Vice Chairman of 🇨🇳 International Development Cooperation Agency, Mr. TANG Wenhong held talks with 🇿🇼 Finance Minister Prof. Ncube in Harare. The two sides discussed ways to boost bilateral cooperation and exchanged letters on two assistance projects by China. https://t.co/ntIuhMhuMM

Mr. TANG Wenhong, Vice Chairman of China International Development Cooperation Agency, paid a courtesy call on H. E. President @edmnangagwa on Thursday. Both sides spoke highly of the fruitful bilateral cooperation that made great contributions to the development of Zimbabwe. https://t.co/u7OV9KQvgL

On 26 October, the China-aided Zimbabwe Parliament Building was officially handed over to H.E. @edmnangagwa by Mr. Tang Wenhong Vice Chairman of CIDCA. H.E. Amb. Zhou Ding and Hon. Chitando signed the handover Certificate on behalf of the two Governments respectively. https://t.co/Yu2ywCjYcS
H.E. @edmnangagwa praised the Building as one of the most magnificent buildings in Zimbabwe, which signifies the excellent relations which exist between Zimbabwe and China.

Mr. Tang Wenhong emphasized that New Parliament Building is not only a full-functioning place for state affairs, but an extraordinary artistic masterpiece, which will also bring along more development opportunities to Harare and its surrounding areas.

Today, 25 Oct. 2023, marks the 5th Anti-Sanctions Day. China once again urges the few countries and organizations to listen to the international call for justice, lift the unlawful sanctions on Zimbabwe as soon as possible. https://t.co/28jTdN9DUf
RT @China_Amb_Zim: Glad to join Hon.@TateMavetera and other dignitaries, in addressing the launch of Huawei's Seeds for the Future 2023. I…

Glad to join Hon.@TateMavetera and other dignitaries, in addressing the launch of Huawei's Seeds for the Future 2023. I congrats Huawei on its fruitful works in 🇿🇼. Hope the program continue to serve as a catalyst in propelling 🇿🇼 digital economy and ICT sector forward. https://t.co/EhIpXQdbvG

🇨🇳🇿🇼trade increased 39.4% YoY to US$2.43 bn in Jan-Sep, surpassing the whole trade volume of 2022, of which Zimbabwe exported US$1.36 bn to China & imported US$1.07 bn from China. China's continually expanding imports contributed an US$29 mln trade surplus for Zim. https://t.co/mRGIlz8DZ3
